-- First Pacific Said to Market $400 Million of 10-Year Bonds at 6.375% Yield
-- Katrina Nicholas
-- 2010-09-20T10:38:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-20/first-pacific-said-to-market-400-million-of-10-year-bonds-at-6-375-yield.html

          
          
             First Pacific Co., the Hong Kong-
listed company with telecommunications and infrastructure
investments, plans to sell $400 million of 10-year bonds to
yield about 6.375 percent, according to a person familiar with
the matter.  
 The notes will price today and the sale is being managed by
Credit Agricole CIB and Standard Chartered Plc, the person said,
asking not to be identified as details are private.  
          
          


  


        